<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,356,785]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,356,381]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
FEMALE. This species can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brothers" authorityYear="2015" box="[866,978,356,381]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pherotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,978,356,381]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pherotilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the compound eye placed in a deep anterolateral furrow on the head. Other useful features were discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[1050,1193,391,416]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="143 - 145" refId="ref59102" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2012) A new species of Rhopalomutilla Andre, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) from South Vietnam. Russian Entomological Journal, 21 (2), 143 - 145." type="journal article" year="2012">Lelej (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Body length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="5.6" valueMin="3.6">3.6–5.6 mm</quantity>
. MALE. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
