<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,356,785]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,688,713]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
Two females were collected in Malaise traps in 
<collectingRegion box="[851,1094,688,713]" country="Thailand" name="Phetchaburi" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Phetchaburi Province</collectingRegion>
. One of these females was still attached to a male 
<emphasis box="[364,469,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">in copula</emphasis>
. The males of this and other mutillid species will be treated in an upcoming paper on new sex associations in Thai 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[478,599,760,785]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
